<plot>The largest storm in recorded history struck Louisiana on August 29, 2005 with 175 mph winds, 30 feet of water, breaching 3 levees, and leaving 80% of New Orleans underwater. To date, 1,383 have been confirmed dead, 230,000 have been displaced from their homes, and 5,000 are still unaccounted for... This compelling documentary details the story of one man displaced by Katrina who is still trying to recover from it's disastrous effects. As one voice, this man speaks for many...</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?058881</url></doc>
